reviewText: Was looking for Might Mouse and Woody and found either. Do not remenber from Childhood the one I saw on this cartoon classes

It wasn't what I expected the cartoons seemed old they were as if we were watching a black and white tV set. Some cartoons were boring so i fast forward through them. I won't not recommend them to any one. Say your money and buy a real mighty mouse or woody wood pecker dvd.
This is just as advertised. Great cartoons. Kids today don't have good cartoons like these classics. I recommend this and all classics.

They do have many older cartoons which are hard to find unless on these formats, so I'm pretty happy with them. As a collector, it was a great addition to my collection and I was ecstastic with the price, with so many brand new collectibles being easily $15. to $20. and up.

was hoping for heckle and jeckle episode but these magpies are a male and female pair, not heckle and jeckle despite the advertising. still if you can get it used for $5 or less it's ain't such a bad deal.

The Cartoons included in the DVD were "early" cartoons. I expected later years such as when they used to have Saturday Cartoon Specials at the local Theaters (...as in "20-Cartoons:. IE: Andy Panda, Mighty Mouse, etc.

The cartoons delivered should have stated the years made to insure the satisfaction of the purchaser, etc, and list a few of those cartoons that were included. Thank You
